      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANA dozen boys and their soccer coach went missing on June 23 after entering the Tham Luang Nang Nom cave system in Thailand's northern Chiang Rai province, prompting a rescue mission that lasted almost an entire month.The boys and their coach were not located until July 2 after having been missing for nine days. The rescue operation ended on July 10 after all 12 boys and their coach has been freed.The following animation shows a rough timeline of how the group was found and rescued from the flooded cave.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Soccer team enters the cave2. Authorities find handprints and footprints at a T-junction inside the cave3. Thai Royal Navy SEAL divers launch rescue operation4. Heavy rains continue, causing flood waters to rise5. Pump is brought in to extract water6. Command center erected at entrance of cave7. Soccer team and coach found8. Extraction of soccer team and coachVOICEOVER (in English): "A dozen boys aged 11 to 16 and their 25-year-old soccer coach went missing on June 23 after entering the Tham Luang Nang Non cave system in northern Thailand.""Authorities discovered footprints and handprints at a T-junction within the cave on June 24. They also found backpacks the group had left behind.""On June 25, Thai Royal Navy SEAL divers launched a rescue operation, bringing with them oxygen tanks and supplies.""However, heavy rains caused flood waters in the cave system to rise, forcing rescuers back.""Operations were put on hold on June 28, as a pump was brought in to begin extracting water.""On July 1, a command center was set up at the entrance of the cave, with oxygen tanks and supplies placed every 25 meters to aid the divers in their rescue efforts.""The team of soccer players and their coach were found on July 2 in an enclave that was some 400 meters behind Pattaya Beach and 800 to 1,000 meters underground.""July 8, rescuers began extracting boys from the cave, with the first four boys emerging within 11 hours. Four more boys were rescued on July 9, and the remaining four boys along with their coach were freed on July 10."SOURCES: Fortune, Business Insiderhttp://fortune.com/2018/07/10/thai-cave-rescue-operation-timeline/http://uk.businessinsider.com/thai-cave-rescue-timeline-how-it-unfolded-2018-7***]]></description>
