      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANThe longest lunar eclipse of this century is expected to take place on July 27 for about 1 hour and 43 minutes, reports Space.com.NASA reports Earth's shadow is made from three different parts, the outer part known as the penumbra, the central part known as the umbra and the antumbra, which is beyond the penumbra and umbra. The moon will reportedly turn a "ruddy brown color" when it enters the umbra.The entire event, from start to finish, will take about four hours.According to Express, this month's moon will be at apogee, at its farthest possible distance from Earth.However, when the moon is at its nearest to Earth, it is called a perigee.According to space.com, the blood moon will be visible in most places, except in north America.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Showing Earth's different shadows.2. Showing the moon turning red when it enters a specific shadow.3. Explaining what an apogee is and where the moon will be.4. Explaining what an perigee is.VOICEOVER (in English): "The Earth's shadow is made from three different parts, the outer part known as the penumbra, the central part known as the umbra and the antumbra, which is beyond the penumbra and umbra.""The moon will turn a 'ruddy brown color,' when it enters the umbra.""According to Express, this month's moon will be at apogee, at its farthest possible distance from Earth.""However, when the moon is at its nearest to Earth, it is called a perigee."SOURCES:AL.com, Space.com., Express, Khaleej Times, NASAhttps://www.al.com/news/index.ssf/2018/07/blood_moon_2018_best_times_pla.htmlhttps://www.space.com/41007-blood-moon-2018-longest-lunar-eclipse-guide.htmlhttps://www.express.co.uk/news/science/982695/Eclipse-2018-Blood-Moon-visible-how-long-total-lunar-eclipse-visiblehttps://www.khaleejtimes.com/international/20180714/centurys-longest-lunar-eclipse-will-occur-this-monthhttps://www.nasa.gov/audience/forstudents/5-8/features/nasa-knows/what-is-an-eclipse-58***]]></description>
