      <title>How Narcan saved Demi Lovato from an overdose</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions or custom animation requests, contact tips@nextanimation.com.tw. Visit http://archive.nextanimationstudio.com to view News Direct's complete archive of 3D news animations.RESTRICTIONS: Broadcast: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWAN Digital: NO USE JAPAN, NO USE TAIWANPop star Demi Lovato is in a Los Angeles hospital after reports indicate she overdosed on an undisclosed drug.The 25-year-old had been with friends at her Hollywood Hills home when she suffered an apparent drug overdose around noon on Tuesday.A source told US Weekly that one of her friends reportedly had Narcan on hand and administered it before paramedics arrived to take the unconscious Lovato to the hospital.Overdoses are caused by excessive opioids, which flood the brain and lock onto opiate receptors, causing insufficient breathing, pinpoint pupils, and unconsciousness.Narcan is used to reverse the effects of an overdose and can be administered in two ways: using a nasal spray or via a syringe injected into the thigh, butt, or arm muscles.According to the U.S. Surgeon General's Office, the emergency medication works by knocking the opioids out of the receptors in the brain, blocking and temporarily reversing the effects for 30 to 90 minutes.Narcan has a high efficacy rate, but doesn't always work when administered too late or when too many drugs are present in the body.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Depiction of Demi Lovato suffering an overdose2. Depiction of Narcan being administered3. Depiction of a synthetic opioid overdose4. Depiction of Narcan as nasal spray5. Depiction of Narcan as injectable drug6. How Narcan reverses an opioid overdose7. Depiction of circumstances in which Narcan is ineffectiveVOICEOVER (in English): "Demi Lovato had been with friends at her Hollywood Hills home when she suffered an apparent drug overdose around noon on Tuesday.""One of her friends reportedly had Narcan on hand and administered it before paramedics arrived to take the unconscious Lovato to the hospital.""Overdoses are caused by excessive opioids, which flood the brain and lock onto opiate receptors, causing insufficient breathing, pinpoint pupils, and unconsciousness.""Narcan is used to reverse the effects of an overdose and can be administered in two ways: using a nasal spray or via a syringe injected into the thigh, butt, or arm muscles.""The emergency medication works by knocking the opioids out of the receptors in the brain, blocking and temporarily reversing the effects for 30 to 90 minutes.""Narcan has a high efficacy rate, but doesn't always work when administered too late or when too many drugs are present in the body."SOURCES: U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, US Weeklyhttps://www.surgeongeneral.gov/priorities/opioid-overdose-prevention/naloxone-advisory.htmlhttps://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/demi-lovatos-friends-saved-her-life-with-emergency-narcan/***]]></description>
